<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Evening posts from Abashi</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=149531" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048704.html">Why Verant needs to drop the "will not post about GM vs player issues" stance.</a><P>

It's all about perception.<P>

<B>I understand your opinion, but individual account issues will not be discussed in the court of public opinion. If the owner of the account wants to contact the Head GM and then post the communications, that is their choice to make those communications public. <P>

People can say anything that they like here in public about why they were banned. Sure, we could get in here and argue each issue, but doing that would be fruitless. There is no information that could be placed on this board that someone couldn't claim was "manufactured", leaving the other side with no further avenue to argue the issue, and having the whole thing devolve into a case of "Yes you did/No I didn't". <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049069.html">XSPARTANX</a><P>

WOw, thats the fastest I've ever seen a post removed!! That'll teach you spartan!! :-)<P>

<B>Your post was deleted because it was a deliberate attempt to make people think that I said something that I didn't. Frankly I don't have time to follow these posts telling people that I didn't write them. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049080.html">Congratulations Verant! You fixed the clipping plane by COMPLETELY BREAKING IT....</a><P>

My clipping plane slider bar doesn't work AT ALL now... I guess thats ONE way to solve a problem...<P>

<B>We didn't make any changes to the clipping plane functionality, just made sure the tolerances were set to the maximum levels in zone headers (where zone-specific data is stored). <P>

Did it happen to be raining when you were testing it?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

All remaining clicks towards the right (suppose to be 100%) do NOTHING.<P>

<B>This might be the misunderstanding that we are experiencing. The clip plane slider is not an indication of a percentage, with the far right being 100% or infinity. The clipping plane slider represents a number of "feet", and that number of feet is constant from zone to zone.<P>

In other words, if the slider goes from zero to 2000 feet, and you are in a zone with a min-clip of 500, and a max-clip of 1000, the left 25% of the slider will do nothing, nor will the right 50%. It's very possible that you can get into some zones where the slider does nothing, for instance, if min and max clip were set to the same value. Other zones may show a difference in the clipping for the entire range of the slider.<P>

The reason that the slider does not represnt a percentage of max is that the user would have to keep adjusting it for every zone that they entered (assuming that they weren't able to do 100% in every zone). For instance, if they can typically see 750ft, and the current zone allows a max clip of 1000ft, and the bar represented a percent, they'd set it at 75%. However, when they went into the next zone that allowed a max clip of 4000ft, the bar is still at 75% causing them the need to adjust it down to about 20% for the game to remain playable.<P>

Min and max-clip values change from zone to zone. The range of the clip slider doesn't.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049084.html">Abashi: Clear and Simple: Karanasplit Yes or No?</a><P>

<B>We're looking into options for Karana now. Whether that will entail bringing up a new split server, or splitting people off to one of the 4 existing underutilized servers we won't know until about the middle of next week.<P>

We also have a situation with Bertox again due to the sort-order defaulting to alpha order for the past few weeks. It now defaults to ordering by population, but Bertox got a fairly large influx of players over that period.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049091.html">New hybrid spell listed incorrectly?</a><P>

I had been hearing about the new hybrid spells on test server and that the Paladin spell, divine force, was a lv 51 spell. I went to my vendor and found that the spell cost (9pp) is in line with the lv 51 spells yet it is labeled as a lv 55 spell. I know that things change but talk about a major letdown when I went and tried to buy the spell =( I hope it was just mislabeled for the paladins and that it will be fixed soon. Afterall, our only lv 51 spell is pacify, hardly worth the pp to buy it.<P>

<B>They are indeed intentionally set to levle 55. All of the hybrid spells put in today are level 55 spells.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049099.html">Mr. Abashi and your excess free time</a><P>

I saw a post about the mobs being able to walk thru doors thing.. Think you could dedicate some of that free time and not make mobs play by rules that we cant play by<P>

<B>Well mobs can't exactly go track down a rogue to open the door for them. And they aren't as intelligent as the average player. They therefore get some special advantages to remain competitive.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049101.html">Bards Steatth NERFED, again!</a><P>

Yes once again bards get a stealth nerf. This time they have nerfed both out lvl 23 song (Selo's Consonant Chain) and our lvl 54 song (Selo's Assonait Strane). Chains used to stop feared mobs at 50% health. Very useful for tight fights when the healer is OOM. Strane used to stop full health mobs when feared when played with a magic lute. Now they do not.<P>

<B>Ack, yes, I meant to announce this.<P>

Basically, NPCs now have a maximum amount that they can be slowed down without being damaged. <P>

There was a particular exploit where two bards could get together, play this song (the level 54 one), and the Fear song, and any NPCs in the effect range would stop dead in their tracks and not fight back when being killed. <P>

I'll announce it in the addendum that I'll post shortly.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

I can understnd fixing 54. But why nerf Chains as well?! The movement debuff on chains is a shadow of its former self.<P>

<B>From what they tell me, the max-slowdown was placed just below that of the best darkness spell, so as only to affect those using the level 54 bard spell. If it's affecting anything else, I'll sit down with the programmer. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049114.html">Small Update: Illusions on PvP Teams Servers</a><P>

<B>Today we put in code to make all illusions (illusion being defined as any spell that makes you look different, such as treeform, wolf form, etc) cancel upon casting an offensive spell on another character on the PvP Teams (VZ/RZ). <P>

We've decided to change it so that the only illusions that will cancel are playable-race illusions (troll, human, ogre, etc.) This will go in in the next patch.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049126.html">Verant to end soloing</a><P>

Read the patch message. They noticed that those in a good class can gain exp much faster by not grouping and blasting static spawns, than take their chancesi n a group somewhere dangerous and get killed. So, instead of fixing the game to do what people obviously want to do, they're changing it so we have to play "their way" (see: the Vision(tm)). We made a stink about nerfing our classes, so they decided instead, to nerf the things we kill. Nice move. Hell with it, AC may suck hard, but I can solo as long as I want.<P>

<B>No Breuter, there's no intention here to "end" soloing, but what we have always said is that soloing should be a more difficult and longer path to advancement, even for those classes designed to be soloable. <P>

These high level 6 minute static and solitary spawns make extended camping (which everyone agrees is boring) a preferred method for advancement.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049141.html">Do you not care about your customers?</a><P>

You posted to get people's opinions on the illusions nerf. This sparked outrage from a great many customers. 2 days later, you implement the change.<P>

I'm very disappointed in how you handled this situation. Especially your comment that YOU feel the nerfs you implement are balanced, and you ignore the input of your players.<P>

You guys have some nerve. There were many ways to fix the mez bug without removing them completely. With every patch I look more and more forward to UO2.<P>

<B>What about all of the people who posted that the change was fine as long as it got rid of the permamez bug? If we leave the bug in there, are we then ignoring them?<P>

With any situation, there will undoubtably be people on both sides of the issue. Choosing to do one thing or another does not mean that we are ignoring the other group or that we don't care about them, just that it is often impossible to implement a change to everyone's satisfaction.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
